				\begin{document}$$OCM = k\frac{1}{{1 + e^{ - a(x - b)} }}$$\end{document}OCM=k11+e-a(x-b)where OCM is the Outbreak Climate Multiplier, b is a critical VPD value defining the function`s inflection point, a is the slope of the function (Fig. 1), k is a multiplier to scale OCM to result in a maximum outbreak probability that corresponds to that of windfelled trees, and x is VPDjj.

To address the uncertainty of parameter definitions, we represented each parameter in Eq. 1 as a distribution function:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
